title: Senior Software Developer(Backend developer)
jobDescription:
Position: Senior Software Developer (Backend web developer)


Job Description:


Your main duties entail designing and developing these applications, necessitating proficiency in problem-solving, solution design, and high-quality coding. You should demonstrate the ability to write functional code with keen attention to identifying defects, alongside being a collaborative team member and effective communicator. If you possess a passion for the .NET framework and software design/architecture, we eagerly anticipate meeting you. Your objective will involve collaborating with internal teams to craft, enhance, and sustain software solutions.


Key Responsibilities:


  • Participate in requirements analysis.
  • Collaborate with internal teams to produce software design and architecture.
  • Write clean, scalable code using .NET/.NET core programming languages.
  • Test and deploy applications and systems.
  • Revise, update, refactor and debug code.
  • Improve existing software.
  • Develop documentation throughout the software development life cycle (SDLC)
  • Serve as an expert on applications and provide technical support.

Technical Skills:


  • Experience using .NET Core 6 +.
  • Experience in developing ASP.NET MVC | ASP.NET Core MVC applications.
  • Senior knowledge of Entity Framework 6. * | EF Core | OOPs |Dependency Injection | Repository Pattern | FTP Deployment | REST API
  • Proficient knowledge in MS-SQL | LINQ | Database design including indexes and data integrity.
  • Familiarity with Kendo UI(Telerik)
  • Experience with cross-browser compatibility testing.
  • Excellent verbal communication skills.
  • Experience in either Angular or React


Education Qualifications: Bachelor's/masters degree in computer science or a related field

Experience: 3 - 7 Years

Location: Vashi, Navi Mumbai

Mode of Work: Work from Office


Selection Process:

Round 1: Online Assessment .

Candidates who qualify in the assessment will proceed to the 2nd round.

Round 2: Face-to-Face Interview
